it gets worse when you try to stop because you probably have some complex about food scarcity and get caught in binge and restrict cycles.

after 10 years of eating disorders the only thing that finally made my weight go consistently down was as follows:

1. spend a while eating literally whatever you feel like
2. do NOT beat yourself up after if you eat too much
3. DO tell yourself that if you eat what you want to eat now, you can still have more or something else later
4. before long youll stop wanting to eat absurd amounts of food and you wont be addicted because you know that junk food is cheap, accessible and you can have it whenever you feel like it but healthy food makes you feel better
